      text: [
        "寒食\n[唐] 韩翃\n春城无处不飞花，\n寒食东风御柳斜。\n日暮汉宫传蜡烛，\n轻烟散入五侯家。",
        "迢迢牵牛星\n迢迢牵牛星，皎皎河汉女。\n纤纤擢素手，札札弄机杼。\n终日不成章，泣涕零如雨。\n河汉清且浅，相去复几许。\n盈盈一水间，脉脉不得语。",
        "十五夜望月\n[唐] 王建\n中庭地白树栖鸦，\n冷露无声湿桂花。\n今夜月明人尽望，\n不知秋思落谁家。"
      ],
      textEn: [
        "Cold Food Festival\n[Tang] Han Hong\nSpring fills the capital with flying blossoms everywhere,\nEast wind sways the imperial willows on Cold Food Day.\nAt dusk, candles are passed down from the Han Palace,\nLight smoke drifts into the homes of the five marquises.",
        "Far, Far Away, the Cowherd Star\nFar, far away, the Cowherd Star,\nBright and fair, the Weaving Maiden across the river.\nSlender, slender, she stretches her pale hands,\nClick, click, she works the loom shuttle.\nAll day long she weaves no pattern,\nHer tears fall like rain.\nThe Milky Way is clear and shallow,\nHow far apart can they be?\nWith just one brimming river between them,\nThey gaze and gaze but cannot speak.",
        "Gazing at the Moon on the Fifteenth Night\n[Tang] Wang Jian\nThe courtyard ground is white, crows roost in the trees,\nCold dew silently wets the osmanthus flowers.\nTonight the bright moon is watched by all,\nBut on whose home does autumn longing fall?"
      ],
