      text: [
        "1948年5月25日，攻城的大炮震撼着整个隆化城，解放隆化的战斗打响了。战士们像潮水一般冲向敌军司令部所在地——隆化中学。嗒嗒嗒……从一座桥上，突然喷出几条火舌，封锁了我军前进的道路。那座桥架在隆化中学墙外的一条旱河上。狡猾的敌人在桥的两侧筑了墙，顶上加了盖，构成了一座暗堡。冲锋的部队被压在一个小土坡下面，抬不起头。冲在最前面的一个战士倒下了。",
        "董存瑞瞪着敌人的暗堡，两眼迸射出仇恨的火花。他跑到连长身边，坚决地说：\u201C连长，我去炸掉它！\u201D\n\u201C连长，我掩护！\u201D战友郅顺义也恳切地说。\n连长和指导员商量了一下，同意了他们的请求。\u201C同志们，扔手榴弹！\u201D连长给战士们下了命令。",
        "董存瑞抱起炸药包，郅顺义背起两兜手榴弹，同时跃出战壕，冲了上去。他们互相配合，郅顺义扔一阵手榴弹，董存瑞就向前跃进几步；郅顺义再扔一阵，董存瑞再跃进几步。跟在后面的战友把一捆捆手榴弹送到郅顺义手里。",
        "敌人的机枪更疯狂了，子弹扑哧扑哧打在董存瑞身边，激起了点点尘土，四周冒起了白烟。董存瑞夹紧炸药包，一会儿忽左忽右地匍匐前进，一会儿又向前滚上好几米。敌人的机枪一齐向董存瑞扫射，在他面前交织成一道火网。突然，他身子一震，左腿中了一枪。他用手一摸，全是血。这时，他离暗堡只有几十米了。他隐蔽在一小块凹地里。郅顺义接二连三地扔手榴弹。趁着腾起的黑烟，董存瑞猛冲到桥下。",
        "董存瑞看看四周，这座桥有一人多高，两边是光滑的斜坡。炸药包放在哪儿呢？他想把炸药包放在河沿上，试了两次，都滑了下来。要是把炸药包放在河床上，又无法炸毁暗堡。就在这时候，嘹亮的冲锋号响了，惊天动地的喊杀声由远而近。在这万分紧急的关头，董存瑞昂首挺胸，站在桥底中央，左手托起炸药包，顶住桥底，右手猛地一拉导火索。",
        "导火索哧哧地冒着白烟，闪着火花，火光照亮了他那钢铸一般的脸。一秒钟、两秒钟……他像巨人一样挺立着，两眼放射着坚毅的光芒。他抬头眺望远方，用尽力气高喊着：\u201C同志们，为了新中国，冲啊！\u201D",
        "巨大的响声震得地动山摇，前进的道路炸开了。战士们冲过烟雾，沿着董存瑞开辟的道路杀向敌军司令部，消灭了全部敌人。胜利的红旗在隆化中学上空迎风飘扬。"
      ],
      textEn: [
        "On May 25, 1948, the siege cannons shook all of Longhua city as the battle for its liberation began. Soldiers surged like a tide toward the enemy headquarters at Longhua Middle School. Rat-tat-tat... Suddenly, tongues of flame shot from a bridge, blocking our army's path forward. The bridge spanned a dry riverbed outside the walls of Longhua Middle School. The cunning enemy had built walls on both sides and added a cover on top, turning it into a hidden bunker. The charging troops were pinned down behind a small slope, unable to raise their heads. The soldier at the very front fell.",
        "Dong Cunrui glared at the enemy bunker, his eyes blazing with hatred. He ran to the company commander and said firmly: 'Commander, let me blow it up!'\n'Commander, I'll provide cover!' his comrade Zhi Shunyi said earnestly.\nThe commander and the political instructor discussed briefly and approved their request. 'Comrades, throw grenades!' the commander ordered.",
        "Dong Cunrui picked up the explosive charge while Zhi Shunyi slung two pouches of grenades onto his back. They leapt out of the trench at the same time and charged forward. They coordinated with each other: Zhi Shunyi would throw a volley of grenades, and Dong Cunrui would dash forward several steps; Zhi Shunyi threw another volley, and Dong Cunrui dashed forward again. Comrades behind kept passing bundles of grenades to Zhi Shunyi.",
        "Enemy machine guns grew more frantic. Bullets hit the ground near Dong Cunrui, kicking up puffs of dust as white smoke rose all around. He clutched the explosives, sometimes zigzagging and crawling, sometimes rolling forward several meters. Enemy machine guns all opened fire on Dong Cunrui at once, weaving a net of fire before him. Suddenly his body jerked — a bullet had struck his left leg. He reached down and felt blood everywhere. He was now only a few dozen meters from the bunker. He took cover in a small hollow. Zhi Shunyi threw grenade after grenade. Seizing the moment as black smoke billowed up, Dong Cunrui dashed to the base of the bridge.",
        "Looking around, Dong Cunrui saw the bridge was taller than a person with smooth slopes on both sides. Where to place the explosives? He tried the riverbank twice, but they slid off. If he placed them on the riverbed, they couldn't destroy the bunker above. Just then, a clear bugle call rang out, and earth-shaking battle cries surged from the distance. In this critical moment, Dong Cunrui stood tall beneath the bridge, raised the explosives with his left hand against the bridge's underside, and pulled the fuse with his right.",
        "The fuse hissed with white smoke and sparks, the light illuminating his steel-like face. One second, two seconds... He stood like a giant, eyes shining with determination. Looking into the distance, he shouted with all his strength: 'Comrades, for New China — charge!'",
        "The massive explosion shook the earth, blasting open the path forward. Soldiers charged through the smoke, following the path Dong Cunrui had opened, and destroyed all enemy forces. The victory flag flew high over Longhua Middle School."
      ],
